  "prompt": "What is colour of water?",
  "response": "Pure water is generally considered to be colorless in small quantities. However, it can appear to have a slight blue tint when viewed in larger volumes, such as in oceans or lakes, due to the absorption and scattering of light. Other factors, such as impurities, suspended particles, or algae, can also affect the color of water, giving it shades of green, brown, or even red in some cases.",
